00:50:04.860 --> 00:50:08.000
So what you're looking at,
these are long channels.

00:50:08.000 --> 00:50:12.100
And just to give you a scale,
this is about a half of a

00:50:12.100 --> 00:50:13.210
millimeter.

00:50:13.210 --> 00:50:15.560
This is about a half a
millimeter square and they go

00:50:15.560 --> 00:50:18.570
all the way down for a length
of about eight inches.

00:50:18.570 --> 00:50:23.850
And then the walls, the interior
walls, are coated

00:50:23.850 --> 00:50:26.400
with a very, very thin
layer of platinum,

00:50:26.400 --> 00:50:27.750
palladium, and rhodium.

00:50:27.750 --> 00:50:29.680
Because these are expensive
metals.

00:50:29.680 --> 00:50:31.440
And it's a surface effect.

00:50:31.440 --> 00:50:35.110
So you get no value if you have
an inch deep of platinum.

00:50:35.110 --> 00:50:37.180
The only stuff that works
is the free surface.

00:50:37.180 --> 00:50:39.390
What you'd really like
is a monolayer.

00:50:39.390 --> 00:50:42.130
But a monolayer of platinum has
no mechanical strength.

00:50:42.130 --> 00:50:45.710
So you put the platinum,
palladium, and rhodium down on

00:50:45.710 --> 00:50:48.820
a catalyst support. and this
stuff is made of a ceramic,

00:50:48.820 --> 00:50:52.180
it's magnesia, alumina silica
that's been extruded like

00:50:52.180 --> 00:50:54.820
pasta, and then fired.

00:50:54.820 --> 00:50:57.340
The technology is absolutely
phenomenal.

00:50:57.340 --> 00:50:58.420
Goes into this.

00:50:58.420 --> 00:51:00.540
And then to get the
platinum-palladium-rhodium

00:51:00.540 --> 00:51:02.640
they have a very
thin acid wash.

00:51:02.640 --> 00:51:06.480
chloroplatinic, chlororhodic
acid, wash, little bit of

00:51:06.480 --> 00:51:10.660
surface tension, holds just a
little bit of water, fire, out

00:51:10.660 --> 00:51:11.680
comes the metal.

00:51:11.680 --> 00:51:13.770
Just thick enough.

00:51:13.770 --> 00:51:16.830
If it's too thick, dilute the
concentration of the acid.

00:51:16.830 --> 00:51:20.020
But use that precious
metal sparingly.

00:51:20.020 --> 00:51:23.540
Platinum hit $2,000 an
ounce last year.

00:51:23.540 --> 00:51:24.950
$2,000 an ounce.

00:51:24.950 --> 00:51:26.846
You steal a car, throw
the car away, and get

00:51:26.846 --> 00:51:28.096
the catalytic converter.

00:51:31.230 --> 00:51:33.890
So anyway, that's underneath.

00:51:33.890 --> 00:51:36.310
That's what's going on
underneath the car.

00:51:36.310 --> 00:51:41.670
And actually, I'm holding for
you the elements of clean air,

00:51:41.670 --> 00:51:42.850
the catalytic converter.

00:51:42.850 --> 00:51:45.210
But the catalytic converter
can't work unless we control

00:51:45.210 --> 00:51:47.540
the air to fuel ratio,
which we have to do

00:51:47.540 --> 00:51:48.570
with an oxygen sensor.

00:51:48.570 --> 00:51:49.660
I'll show you next day.

00:51:49.660 --> 00:51:51.775
And you've got to feed
it into a CPU.

00:51:51.775 --> 00:51:55.300
If you don't have a CPU, it
can't make rapid feedback to

00:51:55.300 --> 00:51:57.610
keep adjusting the air-to-fuel
ratio.

